    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="628"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d628">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">417.41/11</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">British Embassy</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 421</seg>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The British Embassy present their compliments to the Department of State, and
                    have the honour to refer to the Department’s memorandum of the 2nd instant, with
                    regard to certain British claims against the Government of Nicaragua.</p>
                <p>The substance of this memorandum was duly communicated to His Majesty’s
                    Government, and a telegram has now been received from the Foreign Office stating
                    that His Majesty’s Government regret that it is quite impossible for them to
                    reduce the amount of the Legation claims, as agreed upon by an exchange of notes
                    with the Nicaraguan Government, after the claims themselves had been carefully
                    taxed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 19, 1918</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
